# CP1404 Practical Reflection

Write short but thoughtful answers to each of the following.
Replace each `...` with your meaningful answer.

## What have you changed about your process in this subject based on your personal reflection?

I started trying more practical exercises and doing multiple focused practice sessions while programming.

## What do you still need to change in terms of your approach, application, time on task, attitude, etc.?

Learning Methods: I need to do more deliberate practice, re-examining and refactoring old code to improve its efficiency
 and readability.

Practical Application: I need to go beyond course assignments and start practicing subsequent practical exercises.

Time Investment: I need to develop a continuous, distributed learning plan and stick to daily practice.

Learning Attitude: I need to treat errors as necessary problems to be solved and persevere through repeated attempts.

## What are you doing well in the subject so far that you will keep doing?

I have become proficient in effectively utilizing online resources, understanding different approaches, and debugging my
own programs.

## What do you need to stop or change in your work for this subject overall so far?

I changed my habit of passively rereading notes or slides to complete code, and started to truly understand code structure.

## What is one request you have or change you suggest for this subject and/or your IT degree overall?

I hope to learn about multiple solutions to a problem.
